section.p:
Of particular importance is the standard normal distribution.  This is the normal distribution where \mu = 0 and \sigma = 1. Standardizing a variable of any normal distribution produces a new variable with a standard normal distribution.  In other words, if a variable x has a normal distribution with mean \mu and standard deviation \sigma, then
            z = \frac{x - \mu}{\sigma}
        has the standard normal distribution.  Tables (see Figure), calculators, or software will give the area under the standard normal curve for a particular value of z.
